{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = E.A.K. Larissas | nickname = Alcazar | image = Larissa Alkazar.jpg | image_size = 300px | fullname = Ethniko Athlitiko Kentro Larissas | location = {{flagicon|Greece}} [[Larissa]], [[Greece]] | coordinates = {{coord|39|38|55.36|N|22|24|43.60|E|type:landmark}} | broke_ground = 1965 | renovated = 2005 | expanded = | closed = | owner = General Secretariat of Sports | operator = [[PAE AEL FC|AEL]] | surface = Grass | scoreboard = Yes (nonworking) | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = National Stadium "Olympic Winner Crown Prince Constantine" | tenants = [[AE Larissa FC|AEL]] (1965–2010, 2013–2015), [[AE Larissa FC|AEL U-20]] 2015- [[Apollon Larissa F.C.|Apollon Larissa]] 2017- | seating_capacity = 13,108 }} '''Alcazar Stadium''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Larissa]], [[Greece]] part of the '''National Sports Complex of Larissa''' (''Εθνικό Αθλητικό Κέντρο Λάρισας''-Ε.Α.Κ.Λ.). It got its nickname because it is located in the Alcazar park, in Larisa, which was named after the Arabic name for the park which means "The Castle". The stadium was the homeground of the football team [[Larissa F.C.|AEL]] from 1964 to 2010, and from 2013 to 2015. It is currently the home ground of the club's youth squad (U-20) and Football League Club [[Apollon Larissa F.C.]] It holds 13,108 seats and was built in 1965. [[File:ALKAZAR STADIUM.jpg|thumb|820px|center]] {{AEL 1964 FC}}
