{{Infobox football biography |name = Ashar Bernardus |image = |image_size= |caption = |fullname =Ashlar Christopher Bernardus |birth_date={{Birth date and age|df=yes|1985|12|21}} |birth_place=[[Willemstad]], [[Curacao]] |height= 1.75 m |position = [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] |currentclub = [[Centro Dominguito]] |clubnumber = 10 |youthclubs1 = [[Victory Boys]] |years1 = 2003-2006 |clubs1 = [[Victory Boys]] |years2 = 2006-2012 |clubs2 = [[Centro Barber]] |years3 = 2012 |clubs3 = [[Centro Dominguito]] |nationalyears1 = 2011 |nationalteam1 = [[Curaçao national football team|Curacao]] |nationalcaps1 = 14 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |club_update = |national team_update = }}
'''Ashar Bernardus''' (born 21 December 1985) is a football midfielder who currently plays for Centro Dominguito in the Curacao League.<ref>[http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/16217/Ashar_Bernardus.html National-Football-Teams Profile] National Football Teams</ref>
==International career== He made his national debut with the [[Netherlands Antilles national football team|Netherlands Antilles Nation Football Team]] on September 8, 2006 against [[Guyana national football team|Guyana]],with the result of the match 0-5 in Guyana's favor. Bernardus made his first goal with the Netherlands Antilles national team on October 23, 2008, against the [[Cuba national football team|Cuban national team]] in a 7-1 match that resulted in Cuba's victory. On August 19, 2011, Bernardus made his debut with the [[Curaçao national football team]] in a friendly match against the [[Dominican Republic national football team|Dominican Republic]] that [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] lost, 1-0.
