{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Lynn Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | image_size = 220 | caption = | fullname = Dr. Mark & Cindy Lynn Stadium | former names = | location = [[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville]], [[Kentucky]] | coordinates = {{Coord|38.2087|-85.75515|type:landmark_region:US-KY|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = May 3, 2013 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gocards.com/genrel/053013aab.html|title=UofL Breaks Ground on Dr. Mark & Cindy Lynn Soccer Stadium - GoCards.com - Official Website of University of Louisville Athletics|work=gocards.com|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref> | built = | opened = August 1, 2014| | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[University of Louisville]] | operator = [[Louisville Cardinals|University of Louisville Athletic Department]] | surface = Natural turf <ref name="gocards">{{cite web|url=http://www.gocards.com/facilities/lou-facilities-lynn-soccer-stadium.html|title=GoCards.com - Official Website of University of Louisville Athletics - Facilities|work=gocards.com|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref> | scoreboard = | cost = $18.5 million<ref name="gocards" /> | architect = TEG Louisville <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teg123.com/portfolio/uofl--dr-mark--cindy-lynn-soccer-stadium.html|title=Portfolio|work=TEG|accessdate=July 12, 2016}}</ref> | project_manager = TEG Louisville | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = Abel Construction Co, Inc <ref name="teg">{{cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/louisville/news/2013/06/04/architect-wayne-estopinal-talks-about.html|title=University of Louisville soccer stadium to include unique features, Wayne Estopinal says - Louisville - Louisville Business First|date=June 4, 2013|work=Louisville Business First|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref> | main_contractors = | capacity = 5,300 (soccer)<ref name="gocards" /> | suites = 3 (Founders, athletic department and press box)<ref name="gocards" /> | record_attendance = | dimensions = 109.73 x 68.58 m (120 x 75 yards) | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[Louisville Cardinals]] men's and women's soccer | embedded = | website = http://www.gocards.com/facilities/?id=10 | publictransit = }} '''Dr. Mark & Cindy Lynn Stadium''' is a [[soccer-specific stadium]] for college soccer in [[Louisville, Kentucky]]. The stadium was built for the [[University of Louisville]] [[Louisville Cardinals|Cardinals]] Men's and Women's Soccer teams. The teams compete in the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/college/2013/11/13/american-athletic-conference-louisville-reach-agreement-on-breakup-move-to-acc/3518053/|title=AAC, Louisville reach agreement on breakup, move to ACC|author=Jeff Gleer, USA TODAY Sports|date=November 13, 2013|work=USA TODAY|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref>
==Design== The stadium, modeled after [[Sporting Kansas City|Sporting KC's]] [[Sporting Park]]{{citation needed|date=November 2015}}, was designed by TEG Architects, LLC of Louisville.<ref name="teg" /> The stadium seating will include, chairback seating for 2,400 in the main grandstand, bleacher seating for 950 in the east end zone and two berms, which can accommodate 2,400.<ref name="gocards" /> Lynn Stadium will also feature a new 15,320 square foot training center, which will include identical locker rooms for each team (Men's and Women's), coaches' offices and a sports medicine training room.<ref name="gocards" />The complex received LEED Silver certification from the United States Green Building Council (USGBC).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.usgbc.org/projects/ulaa-soccer-facility?view=overview|title=ULAA Soccer Facility {{!}} U.S. Green Building Council|access-date=2016-07-12}}</ref>
