The''' Estadio Akron''', formerly known as the ''' Estadio Omnilife''' and '''Estadio Chivas '''(''Estadio Chivas'', {{IPA-es|esˈtaðjo ˈtʃiβas}}), is a multipurpose stadium that is used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches, including home matches for [[Club Deportivo Guadalajara]], commonly known as the "Chivas". It is part of the J.V.C. complex, and has a [[Seating capacity|capacity]] of 46,232.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.estadioomnilife.com.mx/contenidos/ventajas |title= Estadio Omnilife Ventajas |accessdate=2016-02-05|author= ''Estadio Omnilife''|date= |work= |language= Spanish|cita= }}</ref> Construction started in February 2004, but due to financial problems and other issues, the stadium's completion was delayed for a number of years. 

The stadium hosted its first major international event with the first leg of the [[2010 Copa Libertadores Finals|2010 Finals]] of the [[Copa Libertadores]], and hosted the [[2011 Pan American Games]] [[2011 Pan American Games opening ceremony|opening]] and [[2011 Pan American Games closing ceremony|closing]] ceremonies. The stadium's artificial field caused great controversy, drawing criticism from many notable players, and in May 2012, it was announced that the stadium would replace the artificial turf with natural grass.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/05/16/estadio-omnilife-chivas-pasto-artificial_n_1522884.html|title=Chivas decide quitar el pasto artificial del estadio Omnilife|last=Tovar|first=Sos|date=16 May 2012|website=|publisher=[[Huffington Post]]|language=Spanish|trans-title=Chivas decide to remove the artificial turf from Omnilife Stadium|archivedate=8 December 2017|accessdate=16 May 2012}}</ref>

==History==

[[File:Omnilife Stadium.png|thumb|left|Inaugural match of the Omnilife Stadium vs. [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]]]]

The third public football match at the stadium was a [[exhibition game|friendly]] between Guadalajara and [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 30&nbsp;July 2010. Guadalajara won the game 3–2, with the first goal at the stadium scored by [[Javier Hernández|Javier "Chicharito" Hernández]] playing for Guadalajara.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.jornada.unam.mx/ultimas/2010/07/30/marca-chicharito-hernandez-gol-para-las-chivas|title=Las Chivas derrotan 3–2 al Manchester United|date=30 July 2010|work=[[La Jornada]]|accessdate=2010-07-30|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100802142430/http://www.jornada.unam.mx/ultimas/2010/07/30/marca-chicharito-hernandez-gol-para-las-chivas|archivedate=August 2, 2010|deadurl=yes|agency=[[Notimex]]|language=Spanish|trans-title=Las Chivas defeat Manchester United 3–2}}</ref> Hernández played the entire first half for Guadalajara and switched sides to Manchester United in the second half, symbolically sealing his transfer contract that had been signed in March 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://guadalajarareporter.com/sports-mainmenu-89/26618-manchester-united-set-guadalajara-date.html|title=Manchester United to play Guadalajara at new stadium|last=Marshall|first=Tom|date=8 April 2010|work=Guadalajara Reporter|accessdate=8 April 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711132837/http://guadalajarareporter.com/sports-mainmenu-89/26618-manchester-united-set-guadalajara-date.html|archivedate=11 July 2011|deadurl=yes}}</ref>

