{{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Estádio Nacional do Chiazi | image = | location = [[Cabinda (city)|Cabinda]], [[Angola]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = 2010 | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 20,000 }}
The '''Estádio Nacional do Chiazi''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Cabinda (city)|Cabinda]], [[Angola]]. Completed in 2010, it is used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches. The stadium hosted some events for the [[2010 African Cup of Nations]]. It holds 20,000 people.
