{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Metalurh Stadium | nickname = | image = Kryvyi Rih - Metalurh Stadium.jpg | image_size = 250px | location = [[Kryvyi Rih]], [[Ukraine]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = [[FC Kryvbas Kryvyi Rih]] | seating_capacity = 29,734 ([[football (soccer)|football]]) | dimensions = }}
'''Stadion Metalurh''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Kryvyi Rih]], [[Ukraine]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches, and was the home of [[FC Kryvbas Kryvyi Rih]] (in June 2013 this club went bankrupt).<ref name="FC Kryvbas bankrupt">[http://www.interfax.co.uk/ukraine-news/fc-kryvbas-launches-bankruptcy-procedure/ FC Kryvbas launches bankruptcy procedure], [[Interfax-Ukraine]] (12 June 2013)</ref> The stadium holds 29,734 people.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fckryvbas.com.ua/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=175&Itemid=49 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-05-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110816022207/http://fckryvbas.com.ua/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=175&Itemid=49 |archivedate=2011-08-16 |df= }}</ref>
The station [[Prospekt Metalurhiv (Kryvyi Rih Metrotram)|Prospekt Metalurhiv]] of the [[Kryvyi Rih Metrotram]] is located next to the stadium.
==External links== * [http://www.stadiumguide.com/stadion-metalurh/ www.stadiumguide.com information]
