[[File:CalHurling2013.jpg|300px|thumbnail|right|U.S. NCGAA Hurling Champions 2013 - University of California, Berkeley]] The first ever U.S. National Collegiate Gaelic Athletic Association ([http://ncgaa.org/ NCGAA]) hurling championship took place in 2011. Indiana University won the first championship, beating UC Berkeley 3-4 (13) to 1-6 (9).<ref>http://www.hoganstand.com/usa/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=149684</ref> The University of Montana became the first team to win the championship back-to-back in 2014 and 2015.
The NCGAA Championship is held annually on Memorial Weekend. Winners of the U.S. NCGAA hurling championship include: {| class="wikitable" |- ! Year !! Winner !! Location |- | 2011 || [[Indiana University]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Indiana win first NCGAA championship|url=http://indygaa.com/article.aspx?id=20293291_t3x7545x37|accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Indiana University win first ever National Collegiate Hurling Championship in the U.S.|url=http://www.hoganstand.com/usa/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=149684|accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref> || Gaelic Park, Chicago, IL |- | 2012 || [[Purdue University]] <ref>{{cite web|title=Hurling making a comeback|url=http://www.idsnews.com/news/NewStoryPrint.aspx?id=92665|accessdate=19 June 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130905031209/http://www.idsnews.com/news/NewStoryPrint.aspx?id=92665|archivedate=5 September 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Purdue University win 2012 U.S. National Collegiate Hurling Championship|url=http://www.cacollegesgaa.org/2012/06/01/purdue-take-2012-national-championship/|accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref> || Treasure Island, San Francisco, CA |- | 2013 || [[University of California, Berkeley]]<ref>{{cite web|title=National Collegiate Gaelic Athletic Association|url=http://ncgaa.org/|accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref> || Purdue, Indiana |- | 2014 || [[University of Montana, Missoula]]<ref>{{cite web|title=KPAX Sports|url=http://www.kpax.com/news/montana-hurling-wins-national-championship-in-new-york/|accessdate=10 June 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140611045704/http://www.kpax.com/news/montana-hurling-wins-national-championship-in-new-york/|archivedate=11 June 2014|df=}}</ref> || Gaelic Park, New York |- | 2015 || [[University of Montana, Missoula]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abcfoxmontana.com/story/29152325/griz-hurlers-win-back-to-back-national-titles|title=Griz Hurlers Win Back-To-Back National Titles |accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref> || Missoula, Montana |- |2016 |[[University of Connecticut]] |Boulder, Colorado |- |2017 |[[University of Montana, Missoula]] |Chicago, Illinois |- |2018 |TBD |Boulder, Colorado |}
<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Montana2015.jpg|300px|thumbnail|right|U.S. NCGAA Hurling Champions 2015 - University of Montana, Missoula]] -->
In 2014, a second lower division of the championship known as the Shield was introduced. The University of Pittsburgh won the Shield in 2014, 2015 and 2016.
