{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Negros Occidental Multi-Purpose Activity Center | image = | location = [[Bacolod]], [[Negros Occidental]], [[Philippines]] | owner = [[Negros Occidental]] Provincial Government | surface = 1 hectare | tenants = | seating_capacity = 1000+ }}
The '''Negros Occidental Multi-Purpose Activity Center''' ('''NOMPAC''') is a provincial-owned multi-use [[gym]] located in [[Bacolod City]], adjacent to the [[Capitol Park and Lagoon|Capitol Lagoon]], in [[Negros Occidental]], [[Philippines]]. It is currently used mostly for [[basketball]], [[karatedo]] and [[boxing]] matches.<ref>''Tournament in NOMPAC,''[http://www.sunstar.com.ph/static/bac/2008/10/10/sports/wnu.mustangs.firm.up.champions.league.stint.html Sun Star], September 10, 2008 edition</ref>
Aside from the gym, it also serves as [[emergency evacuation|evacuation]] site of the province during calamities likewise also serves as [[cultural]] facilities in many events and other government related activities like seminars, business and political gatherings.
==External links== *[http://www.negros-occ.gov.ph Official Website of the Provincial Government of Negros Occidental]
